dados.title: WASDE Report
dados.content: WASDE Report SHARE: Facebook Twitter Linkedin World Agricultural Outlook Board WASDE Report About WASDE FAQs and Resources Historical Changes & Revisions Historical WASDE Report Data The World Agricultural Supply and Demand Estimates (WASDE) is prepared and released by the World Agricultural Outlook Board (WAOB). The report is released monthly, and provides annual forecasts for supply and use of U.S. and world wheat, rice, coarse grains, oilseeds, and cotton. The report also covers U.S. supply and use of sugar, meat, poultry eggs and milk, as well as Mexico‚Äôs supply and use of sugar. The WAOB chairs the Interagency Commodity Estimates Committees (ICECs), which include analysts from key USDA agencies who compile and interpret information from USDA and other domestic and foreign sources to produce the report. For more information about the WASDE process and data, visit the WASDE FAQs page. 2026 WASDE Release Dates (12:00pm ET) In 2026 the WASDE report will be released on Jan. 12, Feb. 10, Mar. 10, Apr. 9, May 12, Jun. 11, Jul. 10, Aug. 12, Sep. 11, Oct. 9, Nov. 10, and Dec. 10. February 2026 WASDE Report (Release time: 12:00 PM ET, February 10) PDF XML Excel Text January 2026 WASDE Report PDF XML Excel Text WASDE-Related Content Consolidated Historical WASDE Report Data 2010-2025 (WASDE Report data in .CSV format updated each month, the day after the WASDE release) WASDE Visualization (This visualization is updated each month at 3:00 pm, the day after the WASDE release) Upland and Extra Long Staple Cotton Estimates WASDE Archive (1973 - Present). Weekly Weather and Crop Bulletin Sign up for WASDE‚Äìrelated notifications and other news from WAOB (select the ‚ÄòAg Economics‚Äô mail list).
